The paper proposes a new learning algorithm that improves upon the popular SVM by optimizing the margin distribution, which is characterized by the first- and second-order statistics. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions that the proposed approach can be used in any place where SVM can be applied, which suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions that the approach can be applied to computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE), which are both related to machine learning. Finally, the paper mentions that the approach is verified empirically, which suggests that it may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
